Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC):

The Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) is a structured process used to plan, design, develop, test, deploy, and maintain software. 
It ensures a systematic workflow and helps align software development.
They are 7 pahses avaible in sdlc
* PLAN
* CODE
* BUILD      ---> DEVELOPER
* TEST

* OPERTE
* MONITOR    ---> OPERATIONS
* DEPLOY
